    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1864-06-27T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1864-06-27T00:00:00-05:00" n="48" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d48">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                                Adams</persName>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 1009.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State,</hi>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington,</hi>
                        </placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1864-06-27">
                            <hi rend="italic">June</hi> 27, 1864.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> I acknowledge the receipt of your despatch
                            of the 10th of June, No. 711. I thank you for the clear and candid
                            expression of your views on the subject of our increasing our naval
                            force in European waters.</p>
                <p>The Niagara will appear there before this despatch will arrive. Perhaps
                            all useful purposes may be effected by her presence, together with the
                            Kearsarge. If occasion shall arise, we shall re-enforce them.</p>
                <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Charles Francis Adams,</hi> Esq., <hi rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
